item.dc:creator: @crico11 crico11
item.description:
@crico11 wrote:

if you still have that error on your compiler then you could change the compiler code to this one it works very welll

'@echo off
title Compiler
if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
“%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe” http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit,

1.just copy this code

2.right click on your compiler and press edit

3.paste this code over your old one

item.dc:creator: @DivineSouls DivineSouls
item.description:
@DivineSouls wrote:

right click the compiler, edit it. Replace it with this:

@echo off
@TITLE Blah
echo Compiling…
if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit

If that doesn’t work, you might not have set up your CLASSPATH and your PATH. For a tutorial on how to do so. Follow this:
